{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567009","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567009"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:52:34+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:52:34+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18917"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18917","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18917"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.01,0.03,0.01,0.94]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11650"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80406"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11650","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11650"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18917"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65683"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11349"},{"type":"tags","id":"11358"},{"type":"tags","id":"11364"},{"type":"tags","id":"11365"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27402"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27403"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80406","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80406"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old woman has been caring for her parent who has advanced dementia for the past three years. During a routine appointment, she appears tired and mentions difficulty sleeping. She expresses guilt about sometimes feeling frustrated with her caring responsibilities but is reluctant to accept help.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial response from the healthcare provider?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Recommend immediate placement of the parent in residential care","Suggest she reduce her caring responsibilities","Refer her directly to psychological services","Focus solely on treating her sleep difficulties","Acknowledge the challenges and explore support options"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate response is to \u003Cstrong\u003Eacknowledge the challenges and explore support options\u003C/strong\u003E. This approach validates the carer\u0027s feelings while opening a constructive dialogue about available assistance, which can help prevent carer burnout and maintain sustainable care arrangements.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERecommend immediate placement of the parent in residential care\u003C/strong\u003E - This is too drastic as a first response and doesn\u0027t respect the carer\u0027s wishes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFocus solely on treating her sleep difficulties\u003C/strong\u003E - This addresses only the symptom while ignoring the underlying cause of carer stress\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESuggest she reduce her caring responsibilities\u003C/strong\u003E - This oversimplifies the situation and doesn\u0027t acknowledge the complexity of caring relationships or provide practical solutions\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERefer her directly to psychological services\u003C/strong\u003E - While mental health support may be helpful, immediate referral without first exploring the situation and offering practical support is premature\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare providers should recognise signs of carer fatigue and proactively discuss support options, including respite care, community services, and carer support groups. This helps maintain both carer wellbeing and sustainable care arrangements.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Family carers provide essential unpaid support to patients and should be actively included in healthcare discussions and decision-making.","Carer burden and stress can significantly impact both the carer\u0027s health and their ability to provide care.","Healthcare providers have a responsibility to assess and support carer wellbeing while maintaining patient confidentiality."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 18]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","Ugalde A, Winter N, Sansom-Daly UM, Rhee J, Jongebloed H, Bergin RJ, Livingston PM. Effective integration of caregivers and families as part of the care team for people with cancer. Aust J Gen Pract. 2021 Aug;50(8):527-531. doi: 10.31128/AJGP-03-21-5897. PMID: 34333571. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34333571/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65683"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18917"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65683","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65683"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-20T16:20:11+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-20T16:20:48+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11650"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80406"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemC